cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

This paper analyzes the activity of Wikipedia editors to extract interest profiles of editors from different countries and create a network of significant links between countries with similar interests. This involves techniques from social network analysis, information retrieval, and statistical modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), which are both relevant to the study of online collaboration and information exchange. Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which are also relevant to the study of online communication and information sharing.
